      "operator_entra_id": "alice.chemist@example.com",
      "procedure_text": "To a solution of 4-bromobenzonitrile (100 mg, 0.55 mmol) and phenylboronic acid (80 mg, 0.66 mmol) in toluene/ethanol/water (3:1:1, 5 mL) was added Pd(PPh3)4 (32 mg, 5 mol%) and K2CO3 (152 mg, 1.1 mmol). The mixture was degassed and heated at 85 C for 16 h. After cooling, the mixture was partitioned between EtOAc and water. The organic layer was washed with brine, dried over Na2SO4, concentrated, and purified by silica gel chromatography (hexanes:EtOAc, 9:1) to afford 4-cyanobiphenyl as a white solid (72 mg, 73% yield).",
      "observations": "Clean reaction; no significant homocoupling byproduct by HPLC.",
